1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,020
## [Verse 1]

2
00:00:00,239 --> 00:00:02,153
I opened up the dome at half past ten precisely,

3
00:00:02,153 --> 00:00:26,089
The seeing index: excellent. No cloud. The air was still and nicely

4
00:00:26,089 --> 00:00:33,350
Quiet — so I ran calibration, each alignment checked in turn,

5
00:00:33,350 --> 00:00:40,451
And wrote the date and time and coordinates in the column marked Confirm.

6
00:00:40,451 --> 00:00:47,552
I swept the arc I always sweep at the beginning of the night:

7
00:00:47,552 --> 00:00:52,420
The sky returned each reference point exactly at its right.

8
00:00:52,420 --> 00:00:54,862
## [Pre-chorus]

9
00:00:55,213 --> 00:01:01,835
The Pleiades: present. Virgo's edge: precise.

10
00:01:01,835 --> 00:01:09,334
I checked the catalog against the open field, then checked it twice.

11
00:01:09,334 --> 00:01:16,037
A hundred fixed coordinates exactly where they stood —

12
00:01:16,037 --> 00:01:22,579
The sky was doing what the sky has always understood.

13
00:01:22,579 --> 00:01:22,599
## [Chorus]

14
00:01:22,899 --> 00:01:26,968
And then I found the coordinate.

15
00:01:26,968 --> 00:01:30,478
The gap in the catalog.

16
00:01:30,478 --> 00:01:37,340
The sky was clear. The seeing: exceptional.

17
00:01:37,340 --> 00:01:41,728
I checked the calculation, checked the log.

18
00:01:41,728 --> 00:01:45,399
*Not present at the stated position.*

19
00:01:45,399 --> 00:01:48,031
*Magnitude: nil. Conditions: ideal.*

20
00:01:48,031 --> 00:01:53,936
I looked at everything else, carefully.

21
00:01:53,936 --> 00:01:59,441
That is what you do. That is what is real.

22
00:01:59,441 --> 00:02:00,000
I logged the absence.

23
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:00,956
I logged it like the rest.

24
00:02:00,956 --> 00:02:02,233
With the same hand.

25
00:02:02,233 --> 00:02:04,069
With the same hand.

26
00:02:04,069 --> 00:02:04,149
## [Verse 2]

27
00:02:04,149 --> 00:02:27,048
At two I tracked the double star in Cygnus through the lens and found

28
00:02:27,048 --> 00:02:34,149
Its separation to the arc-minute, which I logged and wrote down.

29
00:02:34,149 --> 00:02:38,138
The Andromeda was rising; I photographed her face —

30
00:02:38,138 --> 00:02:45,159
Two and a half million years of light, arriving at this place.

31
00:02:45,159 --> 00:02:49,467
The light that left before the instruments I work with had a name,

32
00:02:49,467 --> 00:02:57,686
Still crossing all that dark to find the dome, to find the frame.

33
00:02:57,686 --> 00:02:59,441
## [Pre-chorus]

34
00:02:59,441 --> 00:03:05,984
I noted every object in the sweep. I held the instrument still.

35
00:03:05,984 --> 00:03:13,085
The protocol continued. I continued. I was thorough. I was careful.

36
00:03:13,085 --> 00:03:17,313
The sky does not renegotiate the scope of what you're given —

37
00:03:17,313 --> 00:03:26,888
You calibrate, you log, you sweep, and you keep on looking, keep on living.

38
00:03:26,888 --> 00:03:27,366
## [Chorus]

39
00:03:27,366 --> 00:03:31,037
And I found the coordinate.

40
00:03:31,037 --> 00:03:34,548
The gap in the catalog.

41
00:03:34,548 --> 00:03:41,330
The sky was clear. The seeing: exceptional.

42
00:03:41,330 --> 00:03:41,741
I checked the calculation, checked the log.

43
00:03:41,741 --> 00:03:44,181
The night held still. I held still.

44
00:03:44,181 --> 00:03:45,717
I did not stop the log.

45
00:03:45,717 --> 00:03:47,633
*Not present at the stated position.*

46
00:03:47,633 --> 00:03:48,882
*Magnitude: nil. Conditions: ideal.*

47
00:03:48,882 --> 00:03:51,955
*To be reviewed. Assigned a number. Filed.*

48
00:03:52,305 --> 00:03:54,653
And I looked at everything else,

49
00:03:54,653 --> 00:03:54,674
I looked at everything else, carefully.

50
00:03:54,653 --> 00:03:56,104
because the sky is still full.

51
00:03:56,104 --> 00:03:57,556
Because the sky is still full.

52
00:03:57,556 --> 00:03:58,644
And that is what you do.

53
00:03:58,644 --> 00:04:06,383
That is what you do. That is what is

54
00:04:06,383 --> 00:04:09,414
real.

55
00:04:09,414 --> 00:04:12,127
I logged the absence.

56
00:04:12,127 --> 00:04:15,877
I logged it like the rest.

57
00:04:15,877 --> 00:04:17,153
With the same hand.

58
00:04:17,153 --> 00:04:17,632
With the same hand.

59
00:04:17,632 --> 00:04:24,254
## [Bridge]

60
00:04:24,254 --> 00:04:27,925
You should understand the nature of the light.

61
00:04:27,925 --> 00:04:31,596
The light that reaches the instrument is old.

62
00:04:31,596 --> 00:04:33,988
By the time the light arrives here,

63
00:04:33,988 --> 00:04:36,622
the source is what it was —

64
00:04:36,622 --> 00:04:40,213
a very long time ago.

65
00:04:40,213 --> 00:04:43,644
What you are seeing when you look

66
00:04:43,644 --> 00:04:47,793
is the record of the thing.

67
00:04:47,793 --> 00:04:48,350
Not the thing.

68
00:04:48,350 --> 00:04:52,579
This is standard.

69
00:04:52,579 --> 00:04:53,377
This is noted in the protocol.

70
00:04:53,377 --> 00:04:53,617
You note it.

71
00:04:53,617 --> 00:04:54,415
You continue.

72
00:04:54,415 --> 00:04:57,605
You are here to sweep the sky.

73
00:04:57,605 --> 00:04:58,245
The sky is full.

74
00:04:58,245 --> 00:04:59,440
You look at what is there.

75
00:04:59,440 --> 00:04:59,600
## [Final Chorus]

76
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:01,596
So I noted the coordinate.

77
00:05:01,596 --> 00:05:23,536
The gap in the catalog.

78
00:05:23,536 --> 00:05:26,809
The night held still. I held still.

79
00:05:26,809 --> 00:05:31,596
I did not stop the log.

80
00:05:31,596 --> 00:05:34,627
*Not present at the stated position.*

81
00:05:34,627 --> 00:05:38,855
*To be reviewed. Assigned a number. Filed.*

82
00:05:38,855 --> 00:05:41,250
And I looked at everything else,

83
00:05:41,250 --> 00:05:43,483
carefully —

84
00:05:43,483 --> 00:05:46,995
because the sky is still full.

85
00:05:46,995 --> 00:05:48,750
Because the sky is still full.

86
00:05:48,750 --> 00:05:53,377
And that is what you do.

87
00:05:53,377 --> 00:05:56,649
That is what you do

88
00:05:56,649 --> 00:05:58,723
when the sky is still full.

89
00:05:58,723 --> 00:06:00,846
## [Outro]

90
00:06:01,197 --> 00:06:04,228
I closed the dome at first light.

91
00:06:04,228 --> 00:06:08,536
I filed the conditions as: clear.

92
00:06:08,536 --> 00:06:14,521
I wrote the night's total objects: logged.

93
00:06:14,521 --> 00:06:19,149
Everything listed — present.

94
00:06:19,149 --> 00:06:23,059
One gap.

95
00:06:23,059 --> 00:06:24,415
*Position: clear.*

96
00:06:24,415 --> 00:06:30,956
*Expected object: not found.*

97
00:06:30,956 --> 00:06:34,009
*Not found.*
